                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17598186" author="ancosen" created="Wed, 31 Aug 2022 05:54:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You need to bind the cache &quot;cache&quot; to the registry, otherwise in the GET action a cache named &quot;cache&quot; will be re-instantiated from scratch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17598187" author="ancosen" created="Wed, 31 Aug 2022 05:57:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the example with the header it is working just because the endpoint it is the same &quot;caffeine-cache://cache?key=1&quot;, in that case the endpoint will be re-used. In the case of invoking action the endpoint will be different between first and second invocation, so you&apos;ll have a new &quot;cache&quot; cache and the GET won&apos;t return any result.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17598221" author="davsclaus" created="Wed, 31 Aug 2022 07:31:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should make this work the same, so &quot;cache&quot; is not private per endpoint, but we use the component to track caches - this is how we do it in seda and other components.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17598345" author="marat.gubaidullin@gmail.com" created="Wed, 31 Aug 2022 12:05:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Expression support would be also great&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
caffeine-cache:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//${header.cache}?key=${header.key}&amp;amp;action=GET&amp;amp;value=${header.value}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
